description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for Heart Failure Clinical Fellow (ST3+ Grade), to commence in the Department of Cardiology at Homerton University Hospital from August 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Clinical Fellow will work closely with the Consultants, Associate Specialist, Cardiology middle &amp; junior grade medical staff and Cardiology Nurse Specialists, and will support the cardiology team, cardiac nurses and cardiac physiologists, in delivering both in- and out-patient care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Cardiology Department has three permanent and two locum Consultants, one Associate Specialist, three middle grades (one ST3+ and two clinical fellows [ST3+ Grade]) and five junior doctors (one ST1/2, one clinical fellow [ST1/2 Grade], one FY2 and two FY1s). The department offers non-invasive services (ETT, Holter monitor, transcranial Doppler, transthoracic, contrast, transoesophageal and stress echocardiography), and is expanding its heart failure services which encompass a team of community heart failure nurse specialists. The department has close links with St Barthomlew’s Hospital, for invasive cardiac investigation and management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are no on-call commitments for this post. The post is advertised as a six month fixed term position in the first instance, and there is opportunity to extend this term.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameTimothyJob titleCardiology ConsultantEmail addresstimothy.bowker@nhs.netAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To discuss the posts informally please contact the cardiology consultants:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Dutta Roy , Dr TJ Bowker, on 0208 510 5084 / 7033 / 5149&lt;/p&gt;
